UPDATE public.questions SET
  stimulus_text = 'In 1994, the United States Department of Agriculture (USDA) created the "Food Guide Pyramid" to help Americans understand how to make healthy food choices.  The pyramid was designed to show the proportions of different food groups that people should eat each day.  The pyramid was arranged with grains forming the base, followed by vegetables, fruits, and milk products, and with fats, oils, and sweets at the top.   Since then, the USDA has replaced the pyramid with a more complex "MyPlate" graphic.  "MyPlate" uses a plate to visually represent the five food groups: fruits, vegetables, grains, protein foods, and dairy.  The change from a pyramid to a plate has been welcomed by nutrition experts because it ______.',
  question_text = 'Which choice best completes the text with the most logical and precise word or phrase?',
